oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Live from the Pet Milk Grand Ole Opry - 1965-11-27
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of a variety of live shows from the Grand Ole Opry. The recordings feature artist performances by: Roy Drusky (musician), Roy Acuff (musician), Crook Brothers (musicial group), Herman Crook (musician), Jimmie Riddle (musician), Onie Wheeler (musician), Hank Snow (musician), and the Browns (musicial group). The first show is from November 27, 1965. The remaining recordings are from a group of unidentified dates. The tape is labeled the second of thirteen.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Roy Drusky; Roy Acuff; Crook Brothers; Herman Crook; Jimmie Riddle; Onie Wheeler; Hank Snow; Browns
